23/05/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The government has decided to make public 13 out of 27 decrees on the secret services adopted last week. 
The State Gazette published the bills Thursday (22 May) in accordance with the law on security services for improved public control on state intelligence. 
Among other things, the package of new decrees regulates the use of electronic devices for phone tapping and Internet control. 
The package also defines a number of people protected from surveillance, including the president, members of the government, parliament, constitutional and supreme courts, and visiting foreign counterparts. 
(HINA - 22/05/03)
